\section{EXPERIMENTAL RESULTS}
\subsection{Research Questions}
We answer the following research questions (RQs) to assess the quality of Verilog generated given the problems in Table \ref{tab:hdlbits_problems}.
\begin{itemize}
    \item RQ1: How do LLMs without feedback perform (i.e., zero-shot)?
    \item RQ2: Does feedback improve results?
    \item RQ3: Does the number of iterations of feedback impact the quality and number of correct implementations?
    \item RQ4: Does retaining full context from previous iterations impact the quality?
    \item RQ5: Can an ensemble of LLMs improve generation quality at reduced cost?
    \item RQ6: What is the impact of iterative code generation on the cost of use and latency?
\end{itemize}

